# Personas — persona → title keywords   (REQUIRED)
#
# Copy to context/personas.md and fill in. The contact-sourcer turns each persona
# into the title/seniority filters it sends to people_search providers, and the
# qualifier uses these to score contacts. One block per persona.
#
# Tip: include local-language and regional title variants (e.g. German
# "Geschäftsführer" for Managing Director) — providers match on the literal title.
#
# You do NOT have to enumerate every synonym by hand: at brief time the orchestrator
# infers a title equivalence set for the requested role and shows it at Gate #1 (see
# docs/role-expansion.md). Use the optional `Also-known-as:` field below to SEED or pin
# variants you always want — they're unioned with the inferred set and always win.

## Persona: <Economic Buyer>
Titles: [<title keywords, incl. variants>, e.g. "VP Finance", "CFO", "Finance Director", "Kaufmännischer Leiter"]
Also-known-as: [<optional — synonyms to always include, e.g. "Head of Finance", "Finanzvorstand">]
Seniority: [VP, CxO, Director]   # use a vertical-appropriate band — a K-12 principal is a "school-leader", not a "Director"
Why relevant: <one line — what this person owns that makes them buy/champion>
Disambiguation: <how to tell a real match from a false one, e.g. "'Controller' at a
  large enterprise ≈ analyst, not a buyer — require Director+">

## Persona: <Champion / Technical Evaluator>
Titles: [<...>]
Also-known-as: [<optional synonyms>]
Seniority: [Manager, Senior, Director]
Why relevant: <...>
Disambiguation: <...>

## Persona: <User / Influencer>   (optional)
Titles: [<...>]
Seniority: [<...>]
Why relevant: <...>
Disambiguation: <...>
